15/10/2002
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Sulejman Tihic, leader of the Party of Democratic Action (SDA), says the party is open to co-operation with Haris Silajdzic and his Party for BiH. 
According to preliminary results, Tihic is the likely Bosniak member of the BiH Presidency. 
He sees Silajdzic in the second most important position, and urges him to remain in politics despite the election results. 
He also said he accepts all the priorities set by the international community's High Representative, Paddy Ashdown.
In other news, Ashdown announced he would suspend all appointments to positions in state institutions and enterprises until the Agency for Civil Service is ready to perform its duties. 
Meanwhile, the high representative himself will name necessary replacements. 
(OHR Sources, Dnevni Avaz, Vecernji List - 14/10/02)
